post_text:
"Distance learning is in no way an ideal situation, but I think it is really important that we keep sharing the small victories.

On March 23, I didn’t think it would’ve been possible to do group work or keep clubs operating. Yet here we are in September, doing exactly that. Who knows what we will be able to achieve by October."

Thousand Oaks High School senior, Annika, shares her perspective on the start of the 2020-2021 school year via the Thousand Oaks Acorn: https://www.toacorn.com/articles/students-settle-into-a-routine/

FREE Meals will be available for pick-up on Monday through Friday at the following locations and times:

Complete details here: https://bit.ly/3hK8sjv

post_text:
New Support Available - Please Share: Because of physical school closures due to COVID-19, children who are eligible for free or reduced-price meals can get up to $365 in food benefits in addition to their pick up meals from school. These food benefits are called Pandemic EBT or P-EBT.

Families will get up to $365 per eligible child on their P-EBT card to use on food and groceries.

Families with children who get CalFresh, Medi-Cal or Foster Care benefits do not need to apply. Most will get their P-EBT card in the mail during the month of May. P-EBT cards will begin arriving around May 12, 2020.

Families with children who are eligible for free or reduced-price meals and who do not get their P-EBT card in the mail by about May 22, 2020 must apply online before June 30, 2020. The online application will be available beginning May 22, 2020 at ca.p-ebt.org.

*Children can still pick up to-go meals from CVUSD if they have P-EBT benefits

More information about the P-EBT benefit is available here: https://ca.p-ebt.org/info and in Spanish here: https://ca.p-ebt.org/info?locale=es
